1
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:39,300
<i> What did you send me?</i>

2
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:40,733
<i> That's a little reminder</i>

3
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:43,967
<i>that my child's blood
is on your hands.</i>

4
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,300
<i>If you have evidence, go ahead.
File a lawsuit.</i>

5
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,400
<i>You really want to play dirty,
Hazel?</i>

6
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:49,533
<i> What are you going to do?</i>

7
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:50,833
<i> Give me a clue.</i>

8
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:51,833
<i> Manuel.</i>

9
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:55,033
<i>I'm going to use Manuel
against you!</i>

10
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:56,167
<i> Wow, girl.</i>

11
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,133
<i> War freak mode on.</i>

12
00:00:58,267 --> 00:01:01,033
<i>I'm taking her out
of Manuel's life.</i>

13
00:01:01,167 --> 00:01:04,933
<i>About the annulment
with Hazel.</i>

14
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:07,600
<i>Didn't I promise you that
once I got out of the hospital,</i>

15
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:08,933
<i> I'd take care of it?</i>

16
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:09,933
<i> I'd rush everything.</i>

17
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:12,167
<i>It's just so much has happened.</i>

18
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:13,633
<i> I understand.</i>

19
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:15,067
<i> I can wait.</i>

20
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,800
<i>The driver who hit Jessica
is in police custody now.</i>

21
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:20,333
<i>Where is the man who
killed my child?</i>

22
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:21,367
<i> Where is he?</i>

23
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:22,333
<i> You animal!</i>

24
00:01:22,467 --> 00:01:23,567
<i> You monster!</i>

25
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,567
<i> Jessica...</i>

26
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,633
<i>the man who hit you
turned himself in.</i>

27
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:29,033
<i>You'll finally get the justice
you deserve.</i>

28
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:30,200
<i> You can rest now.</i>

29
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:32,500
<i> I'm sorry I couldn't save you.</i>

30
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,100
<i> I know your sister.</i>

31
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:36,733
<i>And I know in my heart,
she doesn't blame you.</i>

32
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:39,900
<i>Not now that justice
is finally hers.</i>

33
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,267
<i> Is this your family?</i>

34
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:44,400
<i>Why do you have a picture
of my wife and kids?</i>

35
00:01:44,533 --> 00:01:46,633
<i> Please don't hurt my family.</i>

36
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:49,233
<i> Don't worry.</i>

37
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:52,300
<i>I just need you to do something
for me.</i>

38
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:57,733
<i>Malabanan released
another statement.</i>

39
00:01:57,867 --> 00:02:00,567
<i>He said he suddenly remembered
someone pushing Jessica.</i>

40
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:04,200
<i>And the description
in the police sketch...</i>

41
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,167
<i> it matched Coleen.</i>

42
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:07,767
<i>What did you say to Timo
after I left?</i>

43
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:08,767
<i> Excuse me?</i>

44
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:11,333
<i>He added details
to his statement.</i>

45
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:12,800
<i> Right after you two talked.</i>

46
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:13,967
<i> What are you implying?</i>

47
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,000
<i> That I coached him?</i>

48
00:02:15,167 --> 00:02:19,633
<i>If Timo really saw Coleen
push Jessica,</i>

49
00:02:19,767 --> 00:02:22,367
<i>why didn't he say it
in his first statement?</i>

50
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,533
<i> Why only now?</i>

51
00:02:23,667 --> 00:02:25,400
<i>Right after your little
private conversation?</i>

52
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:27,867
<i>Instead of saying all these
things, prepare yourself.</i>

53
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
<i>We're filing charges
against Coleen.</i>

54
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,933
<i>This is what we've been
waiting for.</i>

55
00:02:32,067 --> 00:02:33,300
<i> It's finally happening.</i>

56
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:41,267
<i> Thank you, Attorney.</i>

57
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,033
<i> Take care.</i>

58
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,033
<i> Thank you.</i>

59
00:02:44,667 --> 00:02:47,800
<i> You know what? Timo is lying.</i>

60
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:50,633
Yeah. It's so obvious.

61
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:55,467
Mom, Dad...

62
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,333
what did the attorney say?

63
00:02:58,467 --> 00:03:01,867
Is Timo Malabanan
even credible?

64
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,633
He ran off after
hitting Jessica.

65
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:09,400
Attorney Yeban already had
his team investigate him.

66
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:11,867
It turns out Timo
has no criminal record.

67
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,533
Not even a fight
with neighbors.

68
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:15,567
Nothing.

69
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:18,600
People in their village
actually respect him.

70
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:23,667
Sometimes, he even volunteers
as a night watchman.

71
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:28,500
Even his employer,
the owner of the pick-up,

72
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,800
has nothing bad to say
about him.

73
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:35,000
Doesn't that make him
suspicious?

74
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:35,933
Yeah.

75
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,133
Attorney Yeban said
the same thing.

76
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:40,667
He's suspicious
of Timo's motives.

77
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,400
Hazel will definitely use
that statement to file a case

78
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:45,067
against Coleen.

79
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:48,033
And the burden of proof
falls on us.

80
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:54,333
So we need to show
that Timo is lying.

81
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,500
So what do we do, Mom?

82
00:03:56,633 --> 00:04:02,967
If Hazel files the case,
a subpoena will be served.

83
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:06,467
That means we'll have
to file a counter-affidavit.

84
00:04:09,467 --> 00:04:12,333
We need to be ready.

85
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:14,833
Especially Coleen.

86
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:23,033
Felma, I saw you whisper
something to Attorney earlier.

87
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:25,467
What did you tell him?

88
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,067
Who are you?

89
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:50,133
I'm Coleen's mother.

90
00:04:51,733 --> 00:04:52,667
Coleen who?

91
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:57,267
The one you're accusing
of pushing Jessica Cruz.

92
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,667
That's why you hit her.

93
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:02,100
I...

94
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,433
I don't want to talk to you.

95
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:04,967
Sir, take me back to my cell.

96
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,367
I don't need any of this.

97
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,500
Just take me back!

98
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,200
How much did Hazel pay you?

99
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,667
That's insulting, Ma'am.

100
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:19,733
That depends.

101
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:26,367
If what you're saying is true,
you shouldn't feel insulted.

102
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,200
It's not true.

103
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:36,867
Then why did you say
Coleen pushed Jessica?

104
00:05:38,667 --> 00:05:40,300
Because that's what
really happened.

105
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:43,300
What was she wearing?

106
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:49,000
You can't answer?

107
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,567
Because Hazel told you
what to say?

108
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,500
If she didn't even pay you,

109
00:05:55,633 --> 00:06:00,367
then what did she do
to make you lie?

110
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,533
Did she scare you?

111
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:05,333
Threaten your family?

112
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,167
I can help you.

113
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:10,633
I can protect them.

114
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:13,967
Pink.

115
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:16,800
What?

116
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:19,000
She was wearing pink.

117
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,267
Dark blue shorts.

118
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,333
She's the one who pushed Jessica

119
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,200
I don't know her.

120
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:28,900
I only heard the name
because of you.

121
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,900
Sir, I'm done.

122
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,000
We talked already.

123
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:35,967
Can you take me back
to my cell now?

124
00:06:57,967 --> 00:06:59,833
That Timo is lying!

125
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,267
He couldn't even look me
straight in the eye.

126
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,633
It was so obvious.

127
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:06,967
Hazel paid him?

128
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:08,533
What else could it be?

129
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,733
That woman is a demon.

130
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:12,967
See? She pulled it off so well.

131
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,200
So all that screaming
and thrashing at the station

132
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:16,333
was all just an act?

133
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,800
The way she charged at Timo.

134
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:22,200
So how do we prove
Hazel paid him off?

135
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,333
Son, that's going
to be difficult.

136
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:27,300
Only the two of them know
what deal they made.

137
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,933
Andrea, you all need a break.

138
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:37,500
I suggest we push through
with the trip to Laguna.

139
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:42,033
Dad...

140
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:45,033
Mom, maybe we should go ahead

141
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:47,567
with the vacation
Joel and I planned?

142
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:53,067
It might give us a chance
to clear our heads.

143
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:56,133
<i> That actually sounds good.</i>

144
00:07:57,233 --> 00:07:59,333
It'll keep Coleen away
from all this for a while.

145
00:07:59,467 --> 00:08:00,733
She really needs it.

146
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,967
So, when do we leave?

147
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,033
Now.

148
00:08:06,267 --> 00:08:08,467
We need a few days to breathe...

149
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:11,767
to gather the strength
to face everything.

150
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:13,733
<i> Okay.</i>

151
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:15,067
<i> Please keep me updated.</i>

152
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:15,900
Thanks.

153
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:21,800
Yeah, that was my associate.

154
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:25,600
We just got word
from the Fiscal's office.

155
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:30,800
Hazel has officially filed
the case against Coleen.

156
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:32,600
Attorney, what do we do?

157
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:34,767
We don't have a choice.

158
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,400
We face it.

159
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:39,700
We fight and we need to prove
that Coleen is innocent.

160
00:08:40,667 --> 00:08:43,300
If the Fiscal sees
probable cause,

161
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:45,267
the case goes to court.

162
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:50,433
I don't think our youngest
can handle that.

163
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:52,700
Then we have to be strong.

164
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,900
We prepare Coleen.

165
00:08:55,533 --> 00:08:56,767
<i> We all work together.</i>

166
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,733
<i>- Joel! Hey, wait!
- Why?</i>

167
00:09:12,867 --> 00:09:13,833
Why are you going swimming?

168
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:14,700
You still have a wound!

169
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,133
Is that even healed?

170
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:17,133
Yeah, look.

171
00:09:17,867 --> 00:09:18,867
It's healed. See?

172
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,667
Checking to be sure.

173
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:29,867
You two are having fun.

174
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,800
Food's great!

175
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:34,367
Jeffrey and Andrea
are all set, too.

176
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:34,933
<i> Move over!</i>

177
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,900
Kids, come here.

178
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:41,033
Joel, everyone, come eat.

179
00:09:41,167 --> 00:09:41,567
Let's go.

180
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,267
Come on.

181
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,667
Hey, food's ready.

182
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,367
Here, eat.

183
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,200
<i> So good.</i>

184
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,233
Here, eat some more.

185
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,667
Mom, where's the drink?

186
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,967
Didang went to buy some.

187
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:57,033
She should be on her way back.

188
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,900
Eat up, everyone.

189
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:07,700
Mom, Dad...

190
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:10,033
is there something
you want to say?

191
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:11,967
Is that why you organized
a pool party?

192
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:20,200
To be honest, yes.

193
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:22,267
There's something
you need to know.

194
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,600
Hazel filed a case against me,
didn't she?

195
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:30,233
Yes, dear.

196
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:33,600
There's already a subpoena.

197
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,667
But, sweetheart,
you have to fight, okay?

198
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:37,867
We have to fight.
This isn't just your battle.

199
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:39,833
This is our whole
family's fight.

200
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:47,167
Dad, I don't want to go to jail.

201
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,300
No, no, sweetie.

202
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,467
You won't.

203
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,433
We won't let that happen.

204
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:54,267
We're going to fight this.

205
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,000
Yes, dear.

206
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:57,767
You're not alone.

207
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,833
We're all in this together.

208
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,900
<i> So be strong, dear.</i>

209
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:07,033
Hold your head up.

210
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:12,600
Because what you have
on your side is the truth.

211
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,467
Stand by what's real.

212
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,400
Even if they twist it around,
you know it won't change.

213
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:21,067
<i>Do you know why
Hazel is doing this?</i>

214
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:23,800
Because she wants to break
this family.

215
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,433
She wants us torn apart.

216
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,900
Look around you, sweetie.

217
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:29,967
Mom's here.

218
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:30,900
Our brother's here.

219
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,267
Our dad is finally here.

220
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:35,833
We're finally whole again.

221
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:38,500
Hazel already tore us
apart once.

222
00:11:39,267 --> 00:11:41,267
Are you going to let her
do it again?

223
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:50,933
Hazel's using you because
she thinks you're weak.

224
00:11:51,467 --> 00:11:52,667
That you can't fight back.

225
00:11:54,133 --> 00:11:55,433
Are you going to let her win?

226
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:59,067
Don't let her defeat you.

227
00:11:59,967 --> 00:12:01,333
Don't let Hazel win.

228
00:12:02,633 --> 00:12:04,500
She once took me away from you.

229
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:08,567
And now, she wants you to go to
jail to keep you away from me.

230
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,667
Dear, I've already lost Jessica.

231
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:16,200
I can't lose you, too.

232
00:12:16,367 --> 00:12:17,267
Dad, no. I'm not letting
that happen.

233
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:22,400
I'm not letting us be separated
ever again.

234
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,867
I'll fight.

235
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,700
We'll fight.

236
00:12:40,167 --> 00:12:43,133
So you're alleging that
the respondent,

237
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:45,200
Miss Coleen Ruiz Cruz,

238
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:50,600
intentionally pushed Jessica
Capistrano Cruz on the road?

239
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:53,100
Yes, Fiscal.

240
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:55,300
We are filing a complaint
for murder

241
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:59,867
under Article 248
of the Revised Penal Code.

242
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,500
There was evident malice.

243
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:04,700
The act was deliberate.

244
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:09,100
With due respect, Fiscal,
the incident,

245
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:13,200
if it even happened as alleged,
was at worst an accident.

246
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:20,867
My client had no intent
and no malice.

247
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:23,633
A tragedy occurred, yes.

248
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:25,633
But it was not a crime.

249
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,167
Okay.

250
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,733
We will review the evidence

251
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:31,700
to determine if there
is probable cause.

252
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:33,333
She did it on purpose.

253
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,667
She meant to kill Jessica.

254
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:39,300
You pushed her.

255
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:41,600
You meant it.

256
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,067
Fiscal, I did not push Jessica.

257
00:13:47,467 --> 00:13:49,467
We maintain our position,
Fiscal.

258
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,000
We will file
our counter-affidavit

259
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:54,833
within the prescribed time.

260
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,967
You are hereby furnished
a copy of the complaint

261
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:01,100
along with all
supporting evidence.

262
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,367
File your response
within ten working days.

263
00:14:04,933 --> 00:14:07,900
You may also submit
a reply-affidavit, if you wish.

264
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:11,733
If not, the case will be
submitted

265
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:14,733
for resolution
based on submissions.

266
00:14:17,533 --> 00:14:19,933
This is not a courtroom.

267
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,800
This is a fact-finding.

268
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:28,367
I can recommend either dismissal
of the complaint or indictment

269
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:30,933
if probable cause exists.

270
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:33,733
See you in court.

271
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:37,367
That is, if your conscience
can handle it.

272
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:43,900
I hope Jessica haunts
your sleep every night.

273
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,800
We appreciate your time, Fiscal.

274
00:14:54,933 --> 00:14:56,067
We shall comply.

275
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:57,500
That's all for today.

276
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:09,200
Coleen, next time
you're with Hazel,

277
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:11,333
you need to be braver.

278
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:15,633
Don't let her
get into your head, okay?

279
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,200
So, Coleen...

280
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:21,333
Are you ready for prison?

281
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:23,733
Suits a criminal like you.

282
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,467
You've been running
your mouth all day.

283
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,067
Say it again!

284
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,667
Why? It's true.

285
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,633
You're going behind
bars soon, Coleen.

286
00:15:30,767 --> 00:15:32,700
- Better prepare yourself.
- Oh, really? Shut up!

287
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,167
That hurts!

288
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:35,733
What now, huh?

289
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:36,633
Felma, that's enough!

290
00:15:36,767 --> 00:15:37,967
Let go of me!

291
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,633
- You shameless woman!
- Felma!

292
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:41,367
Felma, stop it!

293
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,700
- What now?
- Felma!

294
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:46,067
- You shameless woman!
- Felma!

295
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:50,133
I know you paid Timo to lie
about my daughter!

296
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:50,867
You demon!

297
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,533
What are you talking about?

298
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:53,467
What lies are you making up now?

299
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,600
You won't even spare my child?

300
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:57,933
I'm the one you want,
then face me!

301
00:15:58,067 --> 00:15:59,300
Restrain your mistress, Manuel!

302
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:00,500
Felma!

303
00:16:00,633 --> 00:16:01,967
- Felma, stop it!
- You shameless woman!

304
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,833
You will never win, Hazel.

305
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,967
I will never let my daughter
go to jail.

306
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,500
And I'm going to find out
exactly what you did

307
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:12,667
to make Timo lie.

308
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,433
To fabricate a story
and frame my child!

309
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:17,233
What are you talking about?

310
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:18,333
I don't know anything

311
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:19,100
- about what you're saying!
- Don't lie to me!

312
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:20,200
You demon!

313
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,000
Manuel, restrain your mistress!

314
00:16:22,133 --> 00:16:22,800
Come on, let's go!

315
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:23,867
What?

316
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,733
Attorney, she started it!

317
00:16:25,867 --> 00:16:27,200
That woman is completely
out of line!

318
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,467
Leave her be.

319
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,533
Attorney, thank you
for your time.

320
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:42,300
Attorney, you're here.

321
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:43,433
Yeah. Where have you been?

322
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:45,400
I thought you were
right behind me.

323
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:48,600
Hazel went looking
for trouble.

324
00:16:48,733 --> 00:16:50,167
So, I entertained her.

325
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,600
Mom, you had another
run-in with her?

326
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:55,100
Yes, son. But we'll talk
about that later.

327
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:01,433
Attorney, what's our next move?

328
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:06,533
We respond point by point
to Hazel's accusations.

329
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:11,733
We counter them with truth,
evidence, and consistency.

330
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:17,133
Coleen's counter-affidavit
must be consistent.

331
00:17:18,267 --> 00:17:21,933
The Fiscal will examine it
word for word.

332
00:17:22,067 --> 00:17:26,400
And if this goes to court,
it must remain consistent.

333
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:31,033
No contradictions,
no emotional outbursts.

334
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,233
Just the truth.
Nothing more, nothing less.

335
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:37,667
That's exactly what
we keep reminding her.

336
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:41,400
For now, let's take a break.

337
00:17:41,533 --> 00:17:44,733
- Coleen, how are you?
- This one's for you.

338
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:46,767
I'm okay, Jeffrey.

339
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,133
Just scared.

340
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,233
Because of Hazel.

341
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:56,633
Sweetie, didn't I tell you
not to let Hazel get to you?

342
00:17:56,767 --> 00:17:58,100
When you face her,

343
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:02,333
just remember everything
she's done to this family.

344
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:04,100
How much damage she's caused.
Think of that, and nothing else.

345
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:08,333
We'll monitor
the Fiscal's office.

346
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,000
If a resolution comes out,
I'll know immediately.

347
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:17,100
In the meantime,
we all need to rest.

348
00:18:17,867 --> 00:18:19,767
Especially you, Coleen.

349
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:23,733
You need your strength
for what's ahead.

350
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:26,033
I'm ready, Attorney.

351
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:27,933
That's right, sweetie.

352
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,467
<i> Jessica, let's talk!</i>

353
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,900
<i> Coleen, stop it!</i>

354
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:35,933
<i>- Jessica, please!
- No!</i>

355
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:37,600
<i>- Jessica!
- Let me go!</i>

356
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:38,933
<i> Jessica!</i>

357
00:18:39,067 --> 00:18:41,467
<i> Jessica!</i>

358
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:44,400
<i> Somebody help my sister!</i>

359
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:46,667
<i> Help!</i>

360
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,133
<i> Ambulance!</i>

361
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:50,400
<i> Somebody call an ambulance!</i>

362
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:52,433
<i>You're the reason why
Jessica died.</i>

363
00:18:52,567 --> 00:18:54,567
<i> You pushed her.</i>

364
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,300
<i> See you in court.</i>

365
00:18:57,467 --> 00:19:01,167
<i>That is, if your conscience
can survive it.</i>

366
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:06,200
<i>I hope Jessica haunts you
every night.</i>

367
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,800
Coleen, time to eat.

368
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:21,400
Coleen, the food's
really good today.

369
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:24,933
<i> Coleen?</i>

370
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:28,433
Coleen?

371
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:32,567
<i> Coleen, can you hear me?</i>

372
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,000
<i>Everyone's waiting
for you downstairs.</i>

373
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:51,800
Coleen is taking so long.

374
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:55,333
Have a little patience, son.

375
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:59,000
You know what our youngest
is going through.

376
00:19:59,133 --> 00:20:02,167
Son, if you're hungry, go ahead.

377
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:03,267
No, I'll wait for her.

378
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:09,533
- Mom?
- Yes?

379
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,567
- Mom, I think...
- Where's Coleen?

380
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:14,233
I think she's sleeping
too deeply.

381
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:16,000
I kept knocking.
She was not answering.

382
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:18,200
And Didang's been knocking
for a while, too.

383
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:20,300
Mom, I don't think
she's waking up.

384
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:22,433
Didn't the doctor say
we need to watch her closely?

385
00:20:22,567 --> 00:20:24,233
She's under so much stress

386
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:25,533
that she might do something
to herself.

387
00:20:25,667 --> 00:20:27,333
Oh God.

388
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:29,133
Get the spare key from Didang.

389
00:20:29,267 --> 00:20:31,167
She's getting it now, Mom.

390
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,333
Coleen!

391
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:34,133
Coleen, sweetheart!

392
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:35,133
- Dad, Wait.
- Coleen!

393
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,433
<i> Coleen!</i>

394
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:57,167
<i> Sweetheart, open the door.</i>

395
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:59,833
Come eat with us.

396
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:00,767
<i> Coleen!</i>

397
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:02,533
<i> Coleen, open this door!</i>

398
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:14,767
Coleen!

399
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:15,700
What are you doing?

400
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:16,767
Give me that!

401
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,700
What are you doing?

402
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:20,733
Dear.

403
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:23,333
Dear.

404
00:21:23,467 --> 00:21:25,000
- Coleen?
- Sweetie!

405
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,400
What's this?

406
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:28,433
Dear, what is that?

407
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:31,400
- Sleeping pills?
- Coleen...

408
00:21:31,533 --> 00:21:33,167
Sweetheart, you don't
have to take that.

409
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,767
You don't need to do that!

410
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,333
Come on!

411
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:44,233
Mom, I just wanted
to sleep peacefully.

412
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,167
Coleen.

413
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:50,267
Dear, medicine
isn't the solution.

414
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:52,833
Then what, Andrea?

415
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:58,100
Ever since Jessica died,

416
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,733
I haven't had a single
moment of peace.

417
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:04,133
Every time I close my eyes,
I see her face.

418
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:05,333
Angry and crying.

419
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:13,300
And her mother keeps blaming me.

420
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:14,800
Accusing me.

421
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:19,500
How am I supposed to understand
subpoenas?

422
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:21,333
Or court? Or legal anything?

423
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:26,767
If I get jailed, will that
lessen the guilt I'm carrying?

424
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:36,100
Sweetheart, I don't know
how to take that pain away.

425
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:42,833
Guilt is like a wound.

426
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:45,333
It heals slowly.

427
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:49,333
I don't know when it will fade.

428
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,400
But one thing is certain.

429
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,300
I'm here.

430
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:58,467
We'll help you through this.

431
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:01,133
We'll stay by your side.

432
00:23:01,267 --> 00:23:03,567
Take care of yourself, dear.

433
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:07,933
Do you understand?

434
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:09,567
Do you hear me?

435
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,300
Do you understand?

436
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:13,333
Yes, Mom.

437
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:15,400
Pray, dear.

438
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:16,867
Run to God.

439
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,267
Your heart will feel lighter.

440
00:23:22,433 --> 00:23:27,267
We'll get through
this together.

441
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:31,600
Mom, I wasn't going
to hurt myself.

442
00:23:31,733 --> 00:23:33,733
I promise.

443
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:37,467
I just really wanted to sleep.

444
00:23:42,033 --> 00:23:44,800
I'll talk to Dr. Darla.

445
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:46,500
I'll ask for a prescription,
okay?

446
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:50,700
So you don't take random
over-the-counter pills again.

447
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:54,000
You can do this, sweetie.

448
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:11,300
We're right here.
We're not leaving you.

449
00:24:11,433 --> 00:24:14,933
We even prepared all
your favorite ingredients

450
00:24:15,067 --> 00:24:16,067
for the hotpot.

451
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:16,867
Dear, you want dessert?

452
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:17,767
Ice cream?

453
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:18,667
I can get some later.
Do you want?

454
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:19,500
I'll go.

455
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:21,367
- No, let me.
- Joel, Jeffrey...

456
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:23,067
It's okay. Thank you.

457
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,400
Do you want me to peel
your favorite orange?

458
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:27,467
Thank you for all the effort.

459
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:30,633
For trying to make me
feel better.

460
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,033
If you were really telling
the truth,

461
00:24:32,167 --> 00:24:34,567
then Timo should've said it
in his first statement.

462
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,433
But no, he added details later.

463
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:37,900
Probably because you did
something again.

464
00:24:38,033 --> 00:24:42,500
But isn't it possible that
this time I'm telling the truth?

465
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:45,100
That I have nothing to do
with the driver's statement?

466
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:47,433
You know how stubborn
that woman is.

467
00:24:47,567 --> 00:24:49,367
And you brought
your father to her?

468
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:52,233
Mom, you know I can't refuse dad
right now.

469
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:54,433
Did anything happen
during their talk?

470
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:57,433
Or did that Hazel woman
attack him again?

471
00:24:57,567 --> 00:24:58,900
Actually, it didn't look
like they were fighting.

472
00:24:59,033 --> 00:25:00,533
It kind of looked like
they were getting along.

473
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:01,900
Getting along?

474
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:05,433
When we went home,
Dad seemed okay.

475
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:08,000
She must've done something.

476
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:10,767
But what if Hazel is right?

477
00:25:10,900 --> 00:25:13,733
Manuel, has that woman
brainwashed you?

478
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:15,833
How can we assist you?

479
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:17,067
We're here with
a warrant of arrest.

480
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,200
We're taking your daughter
into custody.
